<hr class="hr-thin">

<section class="l-home-appointments">
  <div class="l-grid-row">
    <div class="l-column-two-thirds">
      <h2 id="phone-and-face-to-face-guidance-coming-soon">Phone and face-to-face guidance
        appointments</h2>

      <p>You can get guidance on your pension options from this website.</p>

      <p>If you prefer to speak to someone, you can talk to an impartial guidance specialist on the
        phone or face to face. They’ll talk about the
        <a href="/6-steps-you-need-to-take">steps you can take</a> to turn your pension pot into
        income for your retirement.</p>

      <p>
        <a href="/appointments"
           class="button">
          Learn about appointments
        </a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<hr class="hr-thin">

<section class="l-home-about">
  <h2 id="pensions-are-changing">Pensions are changing</h2>

  <div class="l-grid-row">
    <div class="l-column-half">
      <p>
        From 6 April 2015 you'll have more freedom over how you take money from
        your pension pot.
      </p>

      <p>These changes affect you if:</p>

      <ul>
        <li>you're <strong>55 or over</strong>, and</li>
        <li>have a pension based on how much has been paid into your pot (a
          <strong>defined contribution pension</strong>).
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p><a href="/pension-types">
        Help with understanding your pension type
      </a></p>

    </div>
    <div class="l-column-half">
      <p>If you have a defined benefit pension - one based on your salary and
        length of time with your employer - you can still get information from
        these organisations:</p>

      <ul class="unstyled-list">
        <li class="unstyled-list__item">
          <a rel="external" href="http://www.pensionsadvisoryservice.org.uk/">The
          Pensions Advisory Service</a>
        </li>
        <li class="unstyled-list__item">
          <a rel="external" href="https://www.moneyadviceservice.org.uk/">
          The Money Advice Service</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<% content_for :after_script do %>
  <script>
    $(function() {
      var duration = 800;
      $('#link-talk-to-a-specialist').on('click', function () {
        $('html, body').animate({
          scrollTop: ($('#phone-and-face-to-face-guidance-coming-soon').offset().top)
        }, duration);
      });

      $('#link-pensions-are-changing').on('click', function () {
        $('html, body').animate({
          scrollTop: ($('#pensions-are-changing').offset().top)
        }, duration);
      });
    });
  </script>
<% end %>
